config ZMK_SOFLE_ESB_BLE_COMPAT
    bool "Provide BLE-peripheral stubs for ESB split peripherals"
    default y if ZMK_SPLIT_ESB && !ZMK_SPLIT_BLE && ZMK_DISPLAY
    help
      The stock nice_view peripheral widget calls into the BLE split
      peripheral API. When the ESB split transport is used instead, that
      API is not compiled. Enable this to provide stubs so nice_view can
      link.

config ZMK_SOFLE_LS0XX
    bool "Use the vendored Sharp LS0XX driver with serial-vcom-inversion"
    default y if ZMK_DISPLAY
    help
      The Zephyr 4.1 in-tree sharp,ls0xx driver does not implement the
      serial-vcom-inversion software VCOM toggling that ZMK 0.4
      enables in the nice_view overlay (see ZMK PR #3294). Without that
      toggle the Sharp memory LCD develops a DC bias that manifests as
      rapid "refresh" flicker. Enable this option to build a vendored
      copy of the upstream LS0XX driver (post-Zephyr 4.4) that honours
      the new DT properties. The vendored driver binds to a unique
      compatible string (`zmk,sharp-ls0xx`) so it coexists with the
      Zephyr in-tree driver; config/nice_view.overlay rewrites the
      nice_view node's compatible to our string.

config ZMK_SOFLE_LS0XX_VCOM_THREAD_PRIO
    int "Priority for the LS0XX VCOM inversion thread"
    default 11
    depends on ZMK_SOFLE_LS0XX
    help
      Matches the value set by upstream ZMK 0.4 in the nice_view
      Kconfig.defconfig (LS0XX_VCOM_THREAD_PRIO=11).
